{"sha": "d96234bed72e1935d8ab9a0c7a7e70027c86ad77", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0NzI0NzEyOmQ5NjIzNGJlZDcyZTE5MzVkOGFiOWEwYzdhN2U3MDAyN2M4NmFkNzc=", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Noah Lev", "email": "camelidcamel@gmail.com", "date": "2021-08-30T02:02:47Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Noah Lev", "email": "camelidcamel@gmail.com", "date": "2021-08-30T02:38:47Z"}, "message": "Retrieve `DefKind` from HIR map to reduce chance of cycles\n\n`tcx.def_kind()` could theoretically invoke another query, which could\ncause an infinite query loop. Accessing the HIR map directly makes that\nless likely to happen.\n\nI also changed it to use `as_local()` (`tcx.def_kind()` seems to\nimplicitly call `expect_local()`) and `opt_def_kind()` to reduce the\nchance of panicking on valid code.", "tree": {"sha": "c0b80db73e86b736b4d6a2604f7e63de15de2d12", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/c0b80db73e86b736b4d6a2604f7e63de15de2d12"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/d96234bed72e1935d8ab9a0c7a7e70027c86ad77", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/d96234bed72e1935d8ab9a0c7a7e70027c86ad77", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/d96234bed72e1935d8ab9a0c7a7e70027c86ad77", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/d96234bed72e1935d8ab9a0c7a7e70027c86ad77/comments", "author": {"login": "camelid", "id": 37223377, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM3MjIzMzc3", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/37223377?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/camelid", "html_url": "https://github.com/camelid", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/camelid/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/camelid/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/camelid/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/us